WorkItem.Description:
The other day, I tried loading from the armory my new DK (with at the time mostly starting area and HP greens). However after loading, it gave me an error. I closed RAWR and tried re-loading. Now every time he splash image shows up, I get a critical error message:
 
---------------------------
 
---------------------------
Rawr encountered a serious error. Please copy and paste this into an e-mail to cnervig@hotmail.com. Thanks!
 
 
 
 
 
Value of '13083' is not valid for 'Value'. 'Value' should be between 'Minimum' and 'Maximum'.
 
Parameter name: Value
 
 
 
   at System.Windows.Forms.NumericUpDown.set_Value(Decimal value)
 
   at Rawr.DPSDK.CalculationOptionsPanelDPSDK.LoadCalculationOptions()
 
   at Rawr.FormMain.set_Character(Character value)
 
   at Rawr.FormMain.get_Character()
 
   at Rawr.FormMain.Calculations_ModelChanged(Object sender, EventArgs e)
 
   at Rawr.FormMain..ctor()
 
   at Rawr.Program.Main()
---------------------------
OK   
---------------------------
 
I've sent the email but I haven't heard any reply from him. Since then I've had to reinstall my RAWR. I even tried to reload my character from the armory again and it worked fine.
WorkItem.Summary: [DPSDK] Critical Error after loading DK character

Comments.Message:
From the big titles on the discussion page
"If Rawr crashes while using the DPSDK model, or you see lots of items with 'Unknown location', re-download Rawr 2.1.9, and make sure that you see "DPSDK v2.1.9.3" on the splash screen."
Also, I'd check your spam folder; I did reply.
Ok I did that and it's seems to be working now. Yea it did get caught in the spam folder. Thanks anyway.
